[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784627093&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784627093&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

I have the following setup.

	A host named ocelot.entmoot.cs.psu.edu
	An MX record for entmoot.cs.psu.edu pointing to isengard.cs.psu.edu

Using sendmail 5.61 mail sent to user@ocelot.entmoot.cs.psu.edu sits in
the queue with:

   AA25361        7 Fri Dec  8 11:25 schwartz
		    (Deferred: Connection refused by ocelot.entmoot.cs.psu.edu)
				     schwartz@ocelot.entmoot.cs.psu.edu

I thought that sendmail would fall back on the MX record.  But this would
not appear to be the case.  Do I need to have a `wildcard' MX record in
order for this to work?

--
Dan Ehrlich &lt;ehrlich@cs.psu.edu&gt;
